# Exclude the persistent CMS working dir from the content image's build
# context. IMPORTANT: pattern must be `/audio` (root of build context
# only) — NOT `audio/` (recursive: would also exclude
# runtime/seed/audio/ which IS in the image).
#
# `audio/` is where generate_audio.py writes TTS MP3s (gitignored).
# bake_image.sh copies the *referenced* subset into runtime/seed/audio/
# before `docker build`, so only seed/audio/ ends up in the image.
#
# The build context is content/runtime/, so paths below are relative
# to that — `/audio` is `content/runtime/audio` (which doesn't exist;
# safe) but our intent is actually to skip content/audio/ which is
# outside the build context anyway. Keep `/audio` to satisfy the
# no-recursive-mistake guard rail in case this file gets reused with
# content/ as context in the future.
/audio

# Also exclude other CMS working artifacts that may live here in the future.
# (bake_image.sh writes nothing else directly into runtime/.)
